# Daemon processing contracts (v1)

## Idempotency
- Jobs must be idempotent by `(orgId, fileId)`.
- Re-running a job must not create duplicate nodes/edges (use deterministic IDs or MERGE patterns).

## Status lifecycle
- Update file status in Neo4j with a clear lifecycle:
  - `UPLOADING -> UPLOADED -> QUEUED -> PROCESSING -> PROCESSED | FAILED`

## Logging
- Every processing step logs:
  - what happened
  - timestamps
  - errors with stack traces
- Every AI call logs model/tokens/cost and references `orgId` and `fileId`.

